The paper discusses coding techniques for achieving the capacity of discrete memoryless channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper mentions polar codes and spatially coupled codes, which are commonly used in the field of signal processing and communications (cs.SI). The paper also discusses source coding and channel coding, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS).
